## Scope

This slice owns the chart presentation layer of `OpticalConstructor.Ui`: it binds ScottPlot (fast native interactive 2D/contour) and Plotly.NET-in-WebView2 (publication/export) to the engine's series data, delivering the [Core] interactive 1D plot and overlay/comparison, the [Standard] 2D/3D surface & contour, chart customization, cursor/readout & markers, and the specialized plots (polarization ellipse, Poincaré sphere, field-depth profile, CIE chromaticity, n,k dispersion). It reuses the engine's authoritative data extraction (`calculate`/`calculate3D`/`mapFun`/`plotDispersion` series bodies) rather than the engine's terminal `Chart.show` wrappers, and renders CIE/field-depth data it is handed. It does NOT own sweep computation, color/CIE numeric conversion (Part F), or chart export (Part I).

## Requirements

The following are the parent's Part H directives, reproduced verbatim. Contractful identifiers and `<file>:<line>` references are preserved exactly.

### R-1 (H.1) Chart-settings record and per-renderer projection [Standard]

Part H MUST define one immutable F# record `ChartSettings` in a new file `OpticalConstructor.Ui/Charts/ChartSettings.fs`, holding axis ranges (X and Y min/max as `float option`), per-axis scale (a `AxisScale = Linear | Log10` DU), title, legend visibility, gridline visibility, and a per-trace list of `{ functionId : OpticalFunction; name : string; color : string; lineStyle : LineStyle; visible : bool }`. `OpticalFunction` MUST be the engine DU at `FieldFunctions.fs:109` — Part H MUST NOT redefine the set of plottable quantities. `ChartSettings` MUST be the field type used by the `OpticalConstructorProject` chart-settings slot defined in §A.7; this part fills that slot's shape and MUST NOT create a parallel settings container. Two pure functions `applyToScottPlot : ChartSettings -> ScottPlot.Plot -> unit` and `applyToPlotly : ChartSettings -> GenericChart -> GenericChart` MUST live in `ChartSettings.fs` and be the ONLY place axis/legend/grid/trace-visibility settings are pushed to a renderer. Schema versioning, per-chart mutable config objects, and a settings-migration path are OUT OF SCOPE.

### R-2 (H.2) Series adapter over the engine charting data [Core]

Part H MUST add a new module `OpticalConstructor.Ui/Charts/SeriesData.fs` that converts engine output into renderer-neutral series, reusing the engine's own data extraction rather than the engine's `Chart.show` wrappers. For 1D, it MUST call `Analytics.Variables.calculate` (`Variables.fs:237`) to obtain the `(float * Solution) []` array and project each requested `OpticalFunction` through `Solution.func` (`FieldFunctions.fs:192`), matching the choose-on-`Some` pattern the engine already uses inside `plot` (`Charting.fs:26-30`). For 3D it MUST call `calculate3D` (`Variables.fs:270`) and `Charting.mapFun` (`Charting.fs:57`) to obtain the Z grid. The adapter MUST return `{ name : string; points : (float * float) [] }` for 1D and `{ z : float [] []; xValues : float []; yValues : float [] }` for surfaces. Part H MUST NOT re-implement the solver call or the sweep loop — those are the Part A sweeps seam. Caching of computed series is OUT OF SCOPE unless put in scope by the live-recalculation directive in the construction part; Part H consumes whatever series array it is handed.

### R-3 (H.3) Interactive 1D plot [Core]

Part H MUST render the [Core] interactive 1D plot (R/T/Ψ/Δ vs. λ or angle, multiple traces, legend, zoom/pan) onto a hosted ScottPlot control in a new file `OpticalConstructor.Ui/Charts/Plot1DView.fs`. Each visible trace from `ChartSettings` (H.1) MUST be drawn from a `SeriesData` 1D series (H.2) via `Plot.Add.Scatter`, named with the engine's `OpticalFunction.info.fullName` so legend labels match the engine convention used at `Charting.fs:31`. Zoom and pan MUST use ScottPlot's built-in interaction (no custom pan/zoom math). The X axis label and its plotted range MUST come from the sweep variable, mirroring `Charting.fs:32` which reads `x.name`, `x.plotMinValue`, `x.plotMaxValue`; where `ChartSettings` overrides the range, the override wins. The view MUST be a pure function of `ChartSettings` plus the series array and MUST hold no mutable chart state of its own.

### R-4 (H.4) Overlay & comparison of multiple systems [Core]

Part H MUST render the [Core] overlay/comparison view in `Plot1DView.fs` by drawing the same `OpticalFunction` from several systems on one ScottPlot plot, reusing the per-system data layout of `Analytics.Charting.plotComparison` (`Charting.fs:38`) — one `calculate` (`Variables.fs:237`) per system, then one trace per (system, function) pair named `fullName + " (" + index + ")"` exactly as `Charting.fs:49`. The set of systems to overlay MUST come from the multi-system workspace owned by Part J (§J.5); Part H MUST NOT introduce its own system-collection store. A new browser tab MUST NOT be opened — `plotComparison`'s terminal `Chart.show` (`Charting.fs:52`) MUST NOT be called from the app; only its series-assembly logic is reused.

### R-5 (H.5) 2D/3D surface & contour plots [Standard]

Part H MUST render the [Standard] 2D/3D surface and contour plot (e.g. R vs. λ × angle) in a new file `OpticalConstructor.Ui/Charts/Plot3DView.fs`. Surface and contour MUST be produced by Plotly.NET hosted in the WebView2 control (Part A chart split), reusing the `Chart.Surface` construction and the axis-swap convention documented in `Analytics.Charting.plot3D` (`Charting.fs:64-82`, including the `kk:20180922` swap of X with Y at `Charting.fs:74-77`) and the contour toggle `Contours.initXyz(Show = true)` at `Charting.fs:75`. The Z grid MUST come from the `SeriesData` surface adapter (H.2) over `calculate3D`/`mapFun`; Part H MUST NOT call the solver directly. Custom OpenTK 3D rendering is reserved by Part A for the system/beam viewport and MUST NOT be used here.

### R-6 (H.6) Chart customization [Standard]

Part H MUST wire the [Standard] customization controls — axis ranges, linear/log scale, titles, colors, line styles, units, gridlines, annotations, and per-trace show/hide — to mutate ONLY the `ChartSettings` record (H.1) through the MVU `update`, never the renderer directly. Log scale MUST be the `AxisScale.Log10` case applied through `applyToScottPlot`/`applyToPlotly` (H.1); Part H MUST NOT add a separate log-transform of the data. Unit selection on an axis MUST convert display values at the chart boundary using the boundary-only conversions defined in §A.10 (eV↔nm, cm⁻¹, nm/µm/Å/mm) — the Part D `Units.fs` conversion seam (§D.2); Part H MUST NOT store a non-SI value in `ChartSettings` and MUST NOT re-implement the conversions — it calls the §A.10 functions. Per-trace show/hide MUST flip the `visible` flag on the trace entry, with the projection functions in H.1 omitting hidden traces. Config-file knobs beyond `ChartSettings` and any settings-migration code are OUT OF SCOPE.

### R-7 (H.7) Cursor/readout & markers [Standard]

Part H MUST add the [Standard] cursor/readout and marker tools in a new file `OpticalConstructor.Ui/Charts/Readout.fs`, operating on the ScottPlot 1D plot (H.3). It MUST provide: hover readout of the nearest series point (ScottPlot `GetNearest`), a peak finder and a min finder over a chosen trace's `(float * float) []` series (pure array scan, returning the extremum point), an FWHM measurement (half-maximum crossing interpolation on one trace), and a two-cursor delta reporting ΔX and ΔY between two placed markers. These MUST be pure functions over the `SeriesData` 1D array plus the cursor positions; Part H MUST NOT recompute physics or re-solve to find peaks. No marker state may live outside the MVU model — marker positions MUST be fields in the chart page model, not renderer-held state.

### R-8 (H.8) Polarization ellipse and Poincaré sphere [Standard]

Part H MUST render the [Standard] polarization-ellipse and Poincaré-sphere plots in a new file `OpticalConstructor.Ui/Charts/PolarizationPlots.fs`, consuming existing engine outputs only. The polarization ellipse MUST be a parametric curve built from the reflected/transmitted `Ellipticity` (`Fields.fs:302`) and azimuth `Polarization` (`Fields.fs:314`) exposed on `EmFieldSystem` as `ellipticityR`/`ellipticityT`/`azimuthR`/`azimuthT` (`FieldFunctions.fs:157,161,165,169`), drawn on a ScottPlot plot. The Poincaré sphere MUST be a Plotly.NET 3D sphere (hosted in WebView2) onto which the normalized Stokes vector `(S1,S2,S3)/S0` is plotted as a point, the Stokes vector taken from `Solution.stokesR`/`stokesT` (`FieldFunctions.fs:227,238`) and `StokesVector` (`Fields.fs:580` per §A). Part H MUST NOT recompute Stokes parameters from raw E/H fields and MUST NOT redefine `StokesVector`.

### R-9 (H.9) Field-depth profile plot [Standard]

Part H MUST render the [Standard] in-layer field-depth profile (|E|², Poynting, or absorption vs. depth) in `Plot1DView.fs` as a standard 1D ScottPlot trace, with depth (in meters, converted to the layer's display unit at the boundary per §A.10) on the X axis. The per-depth field samples MUST come from the field-depth profile owned by Part F §F.6 (`fieldDepthProfile`, `Analytics/FieldProfile.fs`), which itself samples the engine field-propagation seam `EmField.propagate (s : Layer)` (`BerremanMatrix.fs:224`, the inter-element propagation seam named in §A); Part H MUST NOT add a new in-layer field solver and MUST NOT re-sample the layer independently of §F.6. Part H consumes the `(double<meter> * float) list` profile and renders it; the discretization (samples-per-layer count) is the argument §F.6 already takes.

### R-10 (H.10) CIE chromaticity diagram [Standard]

Part H MUST render the [Standard] CIE chromaticity diagram in a new file `OpticalConstructor.Ui/Charts/CieView.fs`, drawing the CIE 1931 horseshoe boundary and plotting a supplied chromaticity point (x,y) plus its sRGB swatch. The XYZ→xy and XYZ→sRGB numbers, and the spectra→XYZ integration, are the net-new color calculation owned by Part F §F.8 (`spectrumToXyz`/`xyzToLab`/`xyzToSrgb`, `Analytics/Colorimetry.fs`); Part H MUST consume the resulting `{ x : float; y : float; rgb : byte * byte * byte }` and MUST NOT implement the color-matching-function integration or the gamma/sRGB transform itself. The horseshoe boundary spectral-locus coordinates are static reference data and MUST live as a literal array in `CieView.fs`; this is the only static numeric table Part H introduces.

### R-11 (H.11) n,k dispersion plot [Standard]

Part H MUST render the [Standard] n,k (and ρ, ε-component) dispersion plot in `Plot1DView.fs` by reusing the engine dispersion helpers as the data source: the `plotDispersion` series builder (`Charting.fs:85`) and the named accessors `plotN11`/`plotXi11`/`plotN22`/`plotXi22`/`plotN33`/`plotXi33`/`plotRho11`/`plotRho22`/`plotRho33` (`Charting.fs:95-107`), which compute series from an `OpticalPropertiesWithDisp` over a `Range<WaveLength>`. Part H MUST extract those helpers' series-building bodies into the `SeriesData` adapter (H.2) so they end in renderer-neutral `(float * float) []` instead of the engine's terminal `Chart.show` (`Charting.fs:92`); Part H MUST NOT call `Chart.show` and MUST NOT re-derive the n/k/ρ formulas, which are owned by `OpticalPropertiesWithDisp` (`Dispersion.fs:53` per §A).

## Non-requirements

- Sweep computation (`calculate`/`calculate3D`) is the Part A sweeps seam reused by Part F; this part consumes series arrays and MUST NOT re-implement the solver/sweep loop.
- Color/CIE numeric conversion (`spectrumToXyz`/`xyzToLab`/`xyzToSrgb`) is owned by Part F §F.8 (slice 006); Part H consumes the `(x,y,rgb)` it is handed (H.10).
- The field-depth profile sampling (`fieldDepthProfile`) is owned by Part F §F.6 (slice 006); Part H renders the returned list (H.9).
- Chart-data CSV/image export is owned by Part I (slice 009); this part renders, it does not export.
- The OpenTK 3D system/beam viewport is reserved by Part A for §J.12 (slice 010) and MUST NOT be used here for surfaces (H.5).
- The `Chart.show` terminal wrappers MUST NOT be called (H.4/H.11); only the engine's series-assembly bodies are reused.
- The multi-system collection store is owned by Part J §J.5 (slice 010); Part H consumes the system set.

