## Testing plan

Gates that apply: `build`, `unit-tests`, `constructor-unit-tests`.

- `build`: solution builds with the `Charts/` files registered, compiling against the FuncUI DSL surface and the ScottPlot/Plotly.NET/WebView2 package surfaces WITHOUT the FuncUI clone dependency (§0 constraint 5). The chart-page model/`update` MUST contain no Avalonia type (P3).
- `unit-tests`: existing `BerremanTests` stays green (`count_at_least` baseline from the prior slice's state-of-the-world).
- `constructor-unit-tests`: `SeriesDataTests.fs` (AC-H1/AC-H3 — 1D adapter reproduces `Charting.plot`'s chosen `(x,y)` pairs; surface Z grid equals `mapFun`); `ReadoutTests.fs` (AC-H6 — peak/min/FWHM/two-cursor on a synthetic series); `ChartSettingsTests.fs` (AC-H4/AC-H5 — projections omit hidden traces, apply `Log10`, unit switch via §A.10 boundary); `PolarizationPlotTests.fs` (AC-H7 — ellipse from `ellipticityR`/`azimuthR`, Poincaré point from normalized `stokesR`). These are headless pure-function/data tests, not renderer-driven.
- Emit the state-of-the-world file with the `gates:` YAML baseline block.

## Risks

- **Medium:** the `SeriesData` adapter must reproduce the exact choose-on-`Some` projection `Charting.plot` uses (`Charting.fs:26-30`) and the `plot3D` axis-swap (`Charting.fs:74-77`); a divergence makes the chart disagree with the engine's own plots (AC-H1/AC-H3). Extract the series-building bodies, not re-derived logic.
- **Medium:** the n,k dispersion helpers (`Charting.fs:85,95-107`) end in `Chart.show`; this slice must lift only their series-building bodies into `SeriesData` and MUST NOT call `Chart.show` (AC-H10).
- **Low:** the `chartSettings` slot must stay anchored under the project root as Part A reserved it.

## Hand-off

State carried to later slices:
- `Charts/ChartSettings.fs` (the `ChartSettings` slot type + `applyToScottPlot`/`applyToPlotly`), `Charts/SeriesData.fs` (renderer-neutral series adapter), `Charts/Plot1DView.fs`, `Charts/Plot3DView.fs`, `Charts/Readout.fs`, `Charts/PolarizationPlots.fs`, `Charts/CieView.fs` exist.
- Part G (slice 007) result overlay refreshes through the same ScottPlot overlay path (`plotComparison` series layout) this slice provides.
- Part J §J.5 (slice 010) supplies the multi-system workspace store the overlay (H.4) reads; Part J §J.8 supplies the chart color palettes surfaced to these renderers.
- Part I (slice 009 §I.7) exports the rendered charts via the chart libraries' own writers; this slice provides the `ChartHandle`-shaped renderer objects.
- The `chartSettings` slot is filled; Part I round-trips it.

Per `arc-runner.system-md`, emit the state-of-the-world file with a fenced YAML `gates:` block:

```yaml
gates:
  berreman_unit_tests: <int>
```
